<div style="background: rgba(100, 0, 0, 0.5);padding: 2px;border: 2px solid white; box-shadow: 0 0 2em white;">
<Center>''Phenomenon 22'' is the 22<sup>nd</sup> phenomenon of '''The Backrooms'''</center>
<span style= "font-family: Comfortaa; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #FF0000, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:30px; color:red"><center>'''Description'''</center></span>
{{Underline|FF0000}}
Phenomenon 22, otherwise known as "Red Entities," is a very unstable and not well understood condition that severely changes the behavior, intelligence, and anger level of infected beings. Creatures affected by this phenomenon develop a characteristic reddish emission on their skin or surface, which is usually found in the areas of muscle tension or activity. Disguised [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]] are the most frequent and known carriers of Phenomenon 22, but the disease also occurs in others.

The level of intensity, duration, and severity of the transformation vary with respect to the entity that is undergoing transformation. However, in each case, there is a universal pattern: the entity becomes hyper-aggressive, displays augmented physical strength, and develops enhanced predatory senses. These creatures are capable of killing with little provocation, frequently attacking anything that moves with mortal efficiency. Their behavior is not merely random; it is systematic, efficient, and highly brutal. The cause of Phenomenon 22 is not known, although the majority of independent field observations refer to a close relationship, where early red-afflicted being populations were initially discovered. 

Some theories suggest that the phenomenon is caused by some unseen environmental anomaly or experimental residue, while others believe that it is infectious under certain conditions. Human infection, although rare, is a confirmed fact. In these cases, Red Entity attack survivors become gradually and irreversibly transformed. Symptoms begin with fatigue and discoloration of the skin, but the body will ultimately become fully reddish. Mental decline occurs, with paranoia, fury, and loss of emotional regulation. Despite these characters having an external appearance similar to [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]], they are actually very different in that they retain coordination, partial awareness, and strategic mobility, rendering them potentially unpredictable. One of the eerie aspects of the disease is this seeming solidarity between afflicted creatures, human and otherwise. These individuals do not fight with one another, implying an underlying instinct, hive-mind behavior, or recognition system. Whether this speaks to a fundamental bond between ailing minds or a biological communique is not yet understood. 

Any contact at all should not be attempted, and active involvement is discouraged with strong emphasis. Survivalists in general all agree avoidance is the best defense. Flickering red light, ghoulish mimicry of human language, or sudden silence where noise once dominated may signal a confrontation. Wanderers should consider any proof of Phenomenon 22 exposure to be a serious hazard. Evacuation should immediately take place, and affected zones should be closed or marked since the condition is potentially more transmissible than first believed. No cure or reversal process has been proven. Wanderers who are not prepared for this phenomenon are likely to not make it, and those who survive might not for long.
</div>
