<div style="background: rgba(100, 0, 0, 0.5);padding: 5px;border: 2px solid white; box-shadow: 0 0 2em white;">
<span style= "font-family: Comfortaa; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #FF0000, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:30px; color:red"><center>'''Stages'''</center></span>
{{Underline|FF0000}}
=== Stage 1 ===
Stage 1 is the initial stage of transformation experienced by any creature exposed to Phenomenon 22, generally after having been attacked by an affected entity or being. Victims begin to report acute feelings of tiredness, with the pronounced symptoms of a drop in circulation efficiency, or it is verbalized as the sensation of blood being drained from the body. Shortly thereafter, there appear some visible signs of physiological change: these include a flushed, sometimes red skin appearance, common with how one would imagine skin reacting to acute stress or overheating. Physiologically, this is mistaken for shock; in reality, it is the beginning of a deeper systemic alteration.

=== Stage 2 ===
Stage 2 is the midpoint of the transformation process, occurring about two hours following the commencement of Stage 1 symptoms. During this stage, the affected wanderer experiences extreme physical exhaustion, which is frequently accompanied by a strong urge to sleep or lose consciousness. The skin tone darkens into a more prominent red, indicating faster advancement. Although the transformation continues, there is some mitigation available, direct applying almond water to skin has been shown to temporarily delay the spread and intensity of the symptoms, though it seldom completely stops the process. Individuals in Stage 2 may demonstrate impatience, short tempers, and brief aggressive outbursts, but they are not deemed entirely hostile or life-threatening. At this point, seclusion and observation are advised, with strict measures in place.

=== Stage 3 ===
Stage 3 is the final and irreversible stage of the transformation. At this moment, the affected individual's entire physiological system changes: their skin, muscle tissue, and even internal organs turn a deep, saturated red. The cellular structure appears denser and abnormally reinforced. Behaviorally, the individual enters a state of unremitting hostility, attacking any type of movement with fatal intent. The only exception to this behavior is when other Stage 3 individuals or red-affected entities are present, in which case they display no animosity, implying a shared recognition or brain synchronization.

Subjects at this stage have incredible physical power, often breaking through wooden barricades or wrenching open reinforced doors. In addition to sheer force, they demonstrate an alarming boost in cognitive function. This includes the ability to imitate human sounds, engage in deceptive conduct, and entice victims by simulating warmth or concern. Containment of Stage 3 patients is considered high-risk and frequently impractical. Following identification, immediate evacuation or neutralization is advised.
</div>
