<div style="background: rgba(100, 0, 0, 0.5);padding: 5px;border: 2px solid white; box-shadow: 0 0 2em white;">
<span style= "font-family: Comfortaa; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #FF0000, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:30px; color:red"><center>'''Survival Guide'''</center></span>
{{Underline|FF0000}}
Phenomenon 22 has an unusually high death rate, therefore thorough survival data is scarce. The great majority of Wanderers who meet afflicted things do not live long enough to produce useful documentation. However, the few known survivors all agree on the same principle: avoid all Red Entities under any circumstances, regardless of curiosity or potential opportunity. Phenomenon 22 is not only extremely hostile, but it also provides creatures with enormous physical power and increased awareness, making confrontation or provocation effectively suicidal. Direct participation is strictly prohibited, as even slight exchanges have been shown to elicit violent responses or speed the transformation process in exposed individuals. The most effective survival strategy is strict avoidance. If you notice evidence of reddish illumination, odd mimicry, or unpredictable hostility, leave immediately. There is currently no known treatment for exposure. Avoid Phenomenon 22 not only to survive, but also to prevent becoming one of them.
</div>
